[src:1890-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1890-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1890-baltimore-orioles-season/1890-baltimore-orioles-season] The **Baltimore Orioles** team left the American Association after the 1889 season and started playing in the minor Atlantic Association.
[src:1890-baltimore-orioles-season/1890-baltimore-orioles-season] However, when the Brooklyn Gladiators ballclub folded mid-way through the 1890 season, the Orioles returned to the AA to finish out the season.
